1.  What is "MY MOUTH" called in French? (a) Mon next (b) Ma bouche (c) Ma tète 
2.  What do you call "MY NOSE" in French? (a) Mon nex (b) Mon nez (c) Mon cou 
3.  What do you call "MY EYEBROW" in French? (a) Mon oeil (b) Mon front (c) Mon sourcil 
4.  Comment s' appelle "Mon cou"en Anglais? (a) My mouth (b) My chin (c) My neck 
5.  Comment s' appelle "Mon menton" en Anglais? (a) My mouth (b) My leg (c) My chin 
6.  What do you call "MY HAIR" in French? (a) Mes cheveux (b) Ma tète (c) Mon front 
7.  Comment s' appelle "FRIDAY" en Français? (a) Lundi (b) Mecredi (c) Vendredi 
8.  What do you call "MY FOREHEAD" in French? (a) Mon sourcil (b) Mon front (c) Mon cou 
9.  Bon après midi means _________ (a) Good morning (b) Good afternoon (c) Good evening 
10. To say "We are delighted to see you" in French, you can simply say __________ (a) Nous sommes enchantés de Vous voir (b) Je suis occupé maintenant (c) Je suis ravi de te voir 
11.  In French, "ENVIE" actually means __________ (a) Happy (b) Desire (c) Appreciation 
12.  What does "TRE BIEN DORMIE?" mean? (a) Good to see you (b) Hope you're doing well (c) Did you sleep well? 
13. What does "BONJOUR PROFESSEUR" mean? (a) Good morning friends (b) Good morning teachers (c) Good morning Madam 
14.  What does "ÀU REVOIR LA CLASSE" mean? (a) Good evening class (b) Good night class (c) Good bye class 
15.  How do you say "I am delighted to see you" in French? (a) Nous sommes enchantés de te voir (b) Nous sommes enchantés de vous voir (c) Je suis ravi de te voir 
16. Levez-vous la classe means what? (a) Class greet (b) Class stand (c) Class sit 
17. Merci beaucoup means _________ (a) Thank you very much (b) Welcome (c) Good night 
18.  Àu revoir Monsieur means _________ (a) Thank you very much Sir (b) Good morning Sir (c) Good bye Sir
19.  Bonjour mes amies means __________ (a) Good morning children (b) Good morning teachers (c) Good morning friends 
20.  What does "Donc aide-moi Dieu" mean? (a) So help me God (b) Trust and obey (c) I am a Nigerian 
21.  What does the sentence "Le Nigeria ne te saluons" mean? (a) I love Nigeria (b) I am a Nigerian (c) Nigeria we hail thee
22.    What does the sentence "Notra drapeau sera symbole" mean? (a) I can't see the symbol (b) Our flag shall be a symbol (c) I want to draw a symbol 
23.   What is "Comme-ci comme-ca" in English? (a) Like this like that (b) Like that like this (c) Like this like this 
24.   To say "Good morning friends" in French you can simply say___________ (a) Bonjour petit (b) Bonjour mes Amie's (c) Bonjour monsieur 
25.   To say "Did you sleep well" in French you can simply say __________ (a) Tre Bien dormie? (b) Comment çava? (c) Comment se àpassé ke travail?
26.  What is "Ferme ta bouche" in English? (a) Close your mouth (b) Open your mouth (c) Clear the bush 
27.  "Repetez encore" means _________ (a) Repeat after me (b) Repeat it again (c) Stand still 
28.    "Oh Dieu de la création" means what in English? (a) Nigeria is a great nation (b) Oh God of all creation (c) We are His creation 
29.   What does comment tu t'apelle? mean in English? (a) What is her name? (b) What is his name? (c) What is your name? 
30.   What does the sentence "Donc aide moi Dieu" mean? (a) Praise the Lord (b) To God be the glory (c) So help me God
